10) Voice-Side Implementation Checklist (Exact)
10.1 Backend checklist
Build an MCP client wrapper that sends JSON-RPC requests to /mcp.
Include Authorization: Bearer <token> when using Agentic Gateway.
Call initialize once at startup/session begin.
Optionally cache tools/list for UI hints and validation.
For each user action, call tools/call with {name, arguments}.
Parse result.content[0].text as JSON.
If result.isError == true or payload success == false, map to user-safe error message.
Maintain a stable session_id for vajra_ask multi-turn continuity.
10.2 Frontend checklist
Capture voice/text input.
Display normal answer text from payload.response.
Render payload.suggestions as clickable follow-ups (if present).
For action tools, show explicit confirmation before submit (recommended).
Display long-running statuses clearly (scan triggered, PR created, no CVEs found, failed).
10.3 Minimal response contract Voice should normalize to
Voice backend should convert all tool outputs into this internal shape:

{
  "ok": true,
  "tool": "vajra_ask",
  "message": "human readable output",
  "suggestions": [],
  "metadata": {}
}
This prevents frontend coupling to tool-specific raw payload variations.

11) What Vajra Handles vs What Voice Handles
Vajra handles
Intent parsing and clarification for conversational asks (vajra_ask).
Query execution over CVE data and docs retrieval.
Remediation orchestration (fix planning, PR creation, scan dispatch).
Returning structured tool payloads over MCP.
Voice handles
User interaction (speech/text UX).
Tool selection policy and confirmations.
Session continuity identifier management.
Parsing MCP response envelopes and rendering outcomes.
Error UX and retry decisions.


